    • Field Detail

      • root

        public TreeNode<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>> root
        A binary search tree (BST) is a sorted ADT that uses a binary tree to keep all elements in sorted order. If the tree is balanced, performance is very good: O(n lg n) for most operations. If unbalanced, it performs more like a linked list: O(n).
